      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Add reset family carryover summaries",
        "body": "## Behavior or issue addressed\n\nDepends on #90239.\n\nWhen a session has been reset/rotated, the active transcript can be clean while the previous reset archive still contains the latest compaction summary. The next embedded-agent prompt therefore starts without the carryover context unless the model/tool explicitly asks for family history.\n\nThis change reuses the session-family transcript resolver from #90239 and injects the latest reset-archive compaction summary into the embedded-agent prompt context before the LLM boundary, but only when the active context does not already contain a compaction summary.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Move the #90239 family/reset transcript target resolver into a shared gateway helper.\n- Keep `chat.history(includeFamily)` on the shared resolver.\n- Pass the current session store path/entry into embedded-agent attempts.\n- Add a prompt-context transform that prepends one `compactionSummary` from reset ancestor transcripts.\n- Skip injection when the active session already has a compaction summary.\n- Cap family transcript read targets before reading files; ancestor targets stop at the cap while current-session targets remain available.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:** When the active post-reset session has no compaction summary but reset-family transcripts have persisted compaction rows, the embedded-agent prompt context should carry the active reset-family summary forward once before the LLM boundary without reading unowned reset archives or every retained lineage target.\n\n**Real environment tested:** Local upstream checkout at `/home/clever/.openclaw/workspace/github/openclaw` on branch `pr-90259`, current head `d4e119813a`, using real TypeScript source modules and temporary on-disk OpenClaw-like session stores/transcripts under `/tmp`.\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n\n1. Created a temporary on-disk session store where `main` points at a clean active session and `usageFamilySessionIds` contains 35 ancestor sessions plus the current session.\n2. Wrote real JSONL transcript files with compaction rows for each ancestor and an active-current compaction row that must be skipped by carryover.\n3. Invoked `resolveSessionFamilyTranscriptReadTargets` and `resolveSessionFamilyCarryoverSummary` from the branch source with `node --import tsx`, outside Vitest.\n4. Re-ran focused Gateway/carryover tests plus prompt snapshots, TypeScript, and whitespace checks.\n\n**Evidence after fix:**\n\nTerminal capture from current head:\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'SMOKE'\n# smoke creates /tmp/openclaw-family-proof-* transcripts and calls branch source modules\nSMOKE\n{\n  \"targetCount\": 31,\n  \"firstTarget\": \"ancestor-proof-00.jsonl\",\n  \"lastAncestorTarget\": \"ancestor-proof-29.jsonl\",\n  \"currentTargetPresent\": true,\n  \"skippedBeyondCap\": true,\n  \"carryoverSummary\": \"Capped carryover 29\",\n  \"carryoverTokensBefore\": 1029\n}\n\n$ npm run test -- src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat-b.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/session-family-carryover.test.ts\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  82 passed (82)\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  6 passed (6)\n\n$ npm run prompt:snapshots:check\nPrompt snapshots are current (7 files).\n\n$ npm run tsgo:test:src\n# passed\n\n$ git diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n\n- The shared resolver stops before reading the whole 35-ancestor lineage: it returns 31 targets, keeping ancestors 00..29 and the current active target.\n- Ancestor 30 and later are not read before final history/prompt budgets (`skippedBeyondCap: true`).\n- Prompt carryover skips the active current compaction row and selects the latest compaction inside the capped family window, `Capped carryover 29`.\n- Gateway `chat.history(includeFamily)` has focused coverage for the same cap behavior and still preserves current-session content.\n- The prompt-boundary transform prepends carryover exactly once and skips raw model runs.\n\n**Implementation safety proof added in this head:**\n\n- Family history reuses `resolveSessionTranscriptResetArchiveCandidatesAsync`, the existing bounded/cached/header-checked reset archive resolver.\n- The family target cap is enforced in `resolveSessionFamilyTranscriptReadTargets`, so it applies to both Gateway `chat.history(includeFamily)` and embedded prompt carryover before transcript reads begin.\n- The cap reserves room for current-session targets so long ancestor lineages do not hide current context.\n\n**What was not tested:** Full end-to-end Telegram reset turn against a live gateway was not run locally. The current-head smoke and tests exercise the real shared resolver and embedded carryover path against real on-disk session artifacts.",
        "branch": "fix/session-carryover-summary",
